### Development Environment Setup

This is a .http file for testing your API endpoints directly in VS Code.
Install the "REST Client" extension to use this file.

### Variables
@apiGatewayUrl = http://localhost:3000
@userServiceUrl = http://localhost:3001
@reportingServiceUrl = http://localhost:3002
@ingestionServiceUrl = http://localhost:8000
@analysisServiceUrl = http://localhost:8001

### API Gateway Health Check
GET {{apiGatewayUrl}}/health

### User Service Health Check
GET {{userServiceUrl}}/health

### Reporting Service Health Check
GET {{reportingServiceUrl}}/health

### Ingestion Service Health Check
GET {{ingestionServiceUrl}}/health

### Analysis Service Health Check
GET {{analysisServiceUrl}}/health

### Test User Registration (if applicable)
POST {{userServiceUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "testpassword123",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### Test User Login (if applicable)
POST {{userServiceUrl}}/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "testpassword123"
}

### Upload Test Document (if applicable)
POST {{ingestionServiceUrl}}/api/documents/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

[File content would go here]
--boundary123--

### Get Analysis Results (if applicable)
GET {{analysisServiceUrl}}/api/analysis/results/test-startup-id